{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, in the Price sentiment analysis, the original labels are re-categorized into \"Positive,\" \"Negative,\" and \"Price Neutral,\" consolidating all nondirectional sentiments under the \"Price Neutral\" label.",
    "This procedure is replicated for the Supply and Demand sentiment analysis.In addition to fine-tuning, we explore the efficacy of few-shot learning with LLMs.",
    "Prompt engineering techniques are used to construct prompts that incorporate one example of each sentiment label.",
    "Specifically, the relevance classification prompt includes an example of both \"Relevant\" and \"Not Relevant\" articles randomly selected from the Demand, respectively.",
    "This few-shot learning approach is evaluated using Llama 3.1, Mistral AI, and EconMistral, with a temperature setting of 1 and a maximum return token limit of 1000.Table 3.3 provides a comprehensive overview of the seven fine-tuned models trained on the OM dataset."
  ]
}